    <h2>Make an emergency kit</h2>
    <p>It’s a good habit to have at least three days’ worth of food and essentials stored in an easy-to-reach part of your home.</p>
    <p>That’s things like medicines, drinking water, non-perishable food and snacks, and extra blankets. You should also keep a torch, batteries and a phone charger close by too.</p>

    <h2>Make a car kit</h2>
    <p>De-icer, scrapers, wiper fluid and anti freeze will all come in handy if you need to drive during a cold snap.</p>
    <p>You might even want to keep some jump leads in the boot in case your car doesn’t start.</p>
    <p>And before going on any journeys, make sure you’ve got some food, water, a torch, your phone and charger, plus a blanket or two with you.</p>
